result.adr_address: 2-14 Temple St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 2-14 Temple St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Hing Kee Claypot Rice

reviews.text: Tasty! The place was a bit busy on a sunny Sunday afternoon, but it was well worth the wait. This restaurant specializes in claypot rice (煲仔飯), and you should definitely order this dish if you love this kind of cuisine. I also recommend their oyster omelet (蠔餅).

Excellent fish fillet (grouper) claypot rice - not a variety I have had before. Recommended.

Also tried the fried oyster cake. Very nice but a bit greasy.

Found it by accident wandering way off from temple street market. Not the cleanest place to eat but food is good. Clay pot rice portion is big, maybe enough for two if you're not very hungry. We ordered one with spareribs and another with an assortment of meats and sausage the first time. One of the aunties helped us with the condiments to season the rice. The second time we ordered pork with salted fish (I liked this one a lot but it may be a bit too fishy for some people). Food here goes very well with beer. The deep fried oysters smelled really good (it was for the people sitting next to us) unfortunately we already ordered two portions of claypot rice. Next time, we will probably order one portion claypot rice and sample a few of the other dishes.

Nice place to start or end for an evening at temple street market. 

Locals seem not that keen on the insanely huge variety of claypot rice choices as compared to the non locals (healthy mixed of tourist from Taiwan, Korea, Japan... and me). 

It may not be the best chicken & octopus claypot rice, oyster omelette, or mantis shrimp available in the area but i had a good time there.

Very bad. Ordered the salted fish with spare ribs and sausage with spare ribs. Sausage tasted like it has gone bad. Salted fish was good(just the salted fish itself). Chrysanthemum drink was good. The CLAYPOT rice was SUPER BAD

result.adr_address: 15號 Temple St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 15號 Temple St, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Hing Kee

reviews.text: Great local cuisine. They actually have about six of the same restaurant side by side. It gets very packed so be ready for that. The food is very good. We had the curry chicken clay pot meal and it was phenomenal. I highly recommend it. We also had some fried noodles which were also very good. They do speak some English so it makes ordering and paying much easier.

Quite tasty! Special cuisine that can be had in night market in Hong Kong. This store has been selling for 30 years, and its unique taste that let people to trace. The service has been better than 10 years that i visited. Highly recommend !

Dirty and tasty. Like how all local Asian places should be. Don't worry, the food and utensils are clean. The store has just patina'd very well over the last 60 years. If you want to experience something in Hong Kong that is hard to get elsewhere, there's no better place than here. Bozaifan (煲仔飯) and oyster pancakes are a must.

Nice place to go when the weather is cool. Open air (but still indoor/covered) seating. Good food, good price. Of course the environment is packed and not the cleanest, but it’s just that type of place. It departs from the typical Temple Street joint in service, where everyone was polite. The beef and egg clay pot rice and the oyster cakes were the highlights.

Traditional Hong Kong flavor! Remember to add more soil sauce if you order a clay-pot dish. As a Taiwanese, I don’t the flavor suits Taiwanese, but you can try one time to experience local life. Enjoy your trip 😃😃😃

result.adr_address: 香港油麻地廟街2-14號
result.name: 興記菜館

reviews.text: 好吃😋

雞粒煲仔飯跟炒青菜一般水準。
水煮牛肉是酸甜辣的綜合口味，跟認知中的重慶水煮牛有期待上的落差。
海鮮芙蓉蛋無味道，只有上面一層芡水有調味，要加醬油才吃的了。
服務不錯、收碗跟加水很勤快，但以這個價位來說，餐點表現還可以有進步空間。

知道他家是香港超人氣店(聽說還是由港必吃店)，而我個人也是很喜歡吃煲仔飯的，既然來台開店(微風南山店)，當然必須造訪。煲仔裡的鍋巴飯很香很有感覺，但是，臘腸怎麼偏軟無口感，感覺比一般市面賣的臘腸飯還不香。排骨煲仔飯也是一樣，我倒不如買一份市面上的豉汁排骨飯蓋在飯上面，可能還更好吃，這兩樣我都無法給太高分數的。蟹粉豆腐很優，比起上海偏甜的料理方式，我更能接受他家鹹香的口感。牛肉湯是港式香料燉的，先不說台灣人適不適合?光是知道要想在台灣賣牛肉湯，沒有三兩三是不行的。可是，蘿蔔是老的，咬下去有絲。湯的口感距離台灣牛肉湯還是有差距，這種湯要在台灣賣，恐怕有重新思考必要。有點失望，他失去了讓我當回頭客的機會。我給它4顆星83分評價。
煲飯還OK，干煸四季豆不錯，但是出菜順序很有問題，我們點鼓汁炒蜆，但居然是所有菜都吃完了，這道菜才出來，是要怎麼單吃，沒飯配就非常的鹹，總之破壞了整體印象

Tasty! The place was a bit busy on a sunny Sunday afternoon, but it was well worth the wait. This restaurant specializes in claypot rice (煲仔飯), and you should definitely order this dish if you love this kind of cuisine. I also recommend their oyster omelet (蠔餅).
